Today is the birthday of Ernest Rutherford
\f1\b0  (1871-1937), New Zealand {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}} and \'93father of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_physics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 nuclear physics}}\cf4 \'94 and\cf2  
\f2\i \cf4 he\'92s
\f1\i0 \cf2  considered to be one of the greatest experimentalist of the history.\
In early work, mainly performed in Montreal (Canada), Rutherford discovered the concept of radioactive {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Half-life"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 half-life}}, the radioactive element radon, and differentiated and named {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_decay"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 alpha}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beta_particle"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 beta radiation}}. \
It is the basis for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 Nobel Prize in Chemistry}} he was awarded in 1908 "for his investigations into the disintegration of the elements, and the chemistry of radioactive substances", for which he was the first Canadian and Oceanian Nobel laureate.\cb1 \
\cb3 Rutherford performed his most famous work after he became a Nobel laureate, when he was already in the now-called University of Manchester. In 1911, although he could not prove that it was positive or negative, he theorized that atoms have their charge concentrated in a very small {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_nucleus"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 nucleus}}, and thereby pioneered the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rutherford_model"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Rutherford model}} of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atom"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 atom}}, through his discovery and interpretation of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rutherford_scattering"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Rutherford scattering}} by the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gold_foil_experiment"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 gold foil experiment}} of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Geiger"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Hans Geiger}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ernest_Marsden"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 Ernest Marsden}}. \
He performed also the first artificially induced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_reaction"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 nuclear reaction}} in 1917. As a result, he discovered the emission of a subatomic particle which, in 1919, he called the "hydrogen atom" but, in 1920, he more accurately named the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proton"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 proton}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \

\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub Rutherford became Director of the Cavendish Laboratory at the University of Cambridge in 1919. Under his leadership the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neutron"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 neutron}} was discovered by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Chadwick"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 James Chadwick}} in 1932 and in the same year the first experiment to split the nucleus in a fully controlled manner was performed by students working under his direction, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Cockcroft"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 John Cockcroft}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ernest_Walton"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Ernest Walton}}. After his death in 1937, he was honoured by being interred with the greatest scientists of the United Kingdom, near {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sir_Isaac_Newton"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Sir Isaac Newton}}'s tomb in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Westminster_Abbey"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Westminster Abbey}}.\
\
\'c9 oggi il compleanno di Ernest Rutherford, uno dei pi\'f9 grandi fisici sperimentali di tutti i tempi. Vince il premio Nobel per la chimica nel 1908 per i suoi lavori sulla disintegrazione degli elementi e la chimica dei materiali radioattivi. \
Si muovette poi in Inghilterra, a Manchester, nel 1911 dove diresse il suo pi\'f9 celebre esperimento che condusse alla scoperta del nucleo atomico. Nel 1917 prende parte alla prima reazione nucleare indotta artificialmente e, una volta diventato direttore dei laboratori Cavendish nel 1919, sotto la sua direzione avviene la scoperta del protone del neutrone nel 1932 da parte di Chadwick. \
Dopo la sua morte, venne onorato come uno dei pi\'f9 grandi scienziati del Regno Unito e riposa ora nell\'92abbazia di Westminster vicino a Sir Isaac Newton. \
